{
  "stem": "15943.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We would have a loaf, a bread that was like a lump of clay.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was made out of the other grains of the, the, you know, the shells, the grains that you would make flour or whatever.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it came out like a lump of clay, the bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this we had to divide for a whole week.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This-- we each had to stay in line to get the rations.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And if you couldn't divide it, you died even quicker because it takes a lot of strength to look at something in front of you when you're dying and say, I'm going to divide it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I'll gonna to eat it tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Not everybody could do it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we would get rations.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Most of the times the vegetables-- there were vegetables delivered to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They had a delaying day until it became rotten, and then they would give it out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We would-- everything was rationed, was rationed to that point that people were literally dying from hunger.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think it was the ghetto government.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I assumed it was the ghetto government because I think what the Nazis shipped into the ghetto-- and why they let that lay there and to become rotten-- if that was an order, if that was-- I don't know why they would let it do it that way, you know.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as far as we knew, it was the ghetto government that would say this is the ration for this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes for children, if there came in some skim milk, not regularly, but they would give it-- some extra ration to children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If something came in, you know, they treated the children, at one time or another, a little, a little bit better.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
